Students practice in working environment where the knowledge and skills acquired during the studies at the university are essential. The problem situations in the working process will be analysed and the applied solving strategies evaluated with the supervisor from the university. In the course of the internship, the job opportunities of one's specialty in an out-of-university work environment are introduced under the guidance of specialists. Practical skills are acquired, real problem tasks are solved, career options in this institution will be introduced. At the end of the internship, an internship report is prepared, in the framework of which a thorough self-analysis of the gained experience is performed. The student presents the most important results of his / her internship in a public seminar to classmates and other interested parties. Participants in the internship are given feedback on coping with the tasks, which allows the student to analyze and make sense of the professional experience gained. If necessary, the organization of the internship is regulated by bilateral or tripartite agreements, which are concluded between the university and the internship partner before the internship takes place.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is for practicing knowledge and skills acquired during the study at the university in working environment outside the university. During the practical experience the student can evaluate if his/her current skills are at the needed level and is aware of his/her future carrer opportunities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the practice the student: (1) can plan his/her practical work schedule and understand the aims of the practical work (2) have gained practical work experience; (3) is able to work in a team; (4) is able to adapt to the daily work routines; (5) has an overview of a particular institution/company, its operating environment, market potential, career opportunities in this company, as well as company-specific practical aspects of corporate governance; (6) is able to give a report about his activities in the company: problem setup, goals of the training, specific task of the trainee, the results of work; (7) is able to analyze what practical knowledge can he/she apply in his/her following career/job; (9) makes career choices (finds suitable specialization, topic for thesis, or a job); (9) is able to do periodic self-reflection about his/her practical work experience and career-plans.
